==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Univalent
<hw>U*niv"a*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ L. <ets>valens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Valence</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having a valence of
one; capable of combining with, or of being substituted for, one atom of
hydrogen; monovalent; -- said of certain atoms and radicals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Univalve</ent>⟦br⟧
